Preconditions:
- The input array `machines` is not null.
- The length of the input array `machines` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The length of the input array `machines` is less than or equal to 10^4.
- The elements of the input array `machines` are non-negative integers.
- The number of dresses in each washing machine is less than or equal to 10^5.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum number of moves required to make all the washing machines have the same number of dresses.
- If it is not possible to make all the washing machines have the same number of dresses, the method returns -1.